This paper deals with the study of chromatic polynomials, which is a topic in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves algorithms and computational difficulties, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of graphs and their properties also falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and the use of estimation methods suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
